## [FAIL] HIGH — `gridImageDataUrls` undefined in grid-cover ImageGrid call (A4b)

**What the spec writes:**
```ts
<ImageGrid
  cols={gridSpec.columns}
  images={gridSpec.cells}
  dataUrls={gridImageDataUrls ?? safeGridImages.map(() => null)}
  maxHeight={GRID_MAX_HEIGHT_COVER}
/>
```

**What a developer will implement incorrectly:**
The spec uses `gridImageDataUrls` as if it's already in scope within the new `slide.kind === "grid" && slide.isFirst` branch, but never defines where it comes from. The VORHER comment writes `dataUrls={...}` as a placeholder — obscuring the actual existing variable name. The NACHHER code introduces `gridImageDataUrls` without an assignment or import statement.

A developer who creates the new isFirst-branch from scratch will get a TypeScript `TS2304: Cannot find name 'gridImageDataUrls'` error and be forced to reverse-engineer the variable name from the unchanged pure-image branch. If they guess wrong (e.g., `slide.imageDataUrls` vs `slide.gridImageDataUrls`), they either get a compile error or silently pass `undefined` for all data URLs, rendering the cover grid without images.

**Missing:** The spec must either (a) show the correct variable assignment at the top of the grid-cover branch (e.g., `const gridImageDataUrls = slide.gridImageDataUrls;`) or (b) explicitly state the existing variable name that holds per-image data-URLs in the current kind="grid" rendering code.

