## [FAIL] HIGH — Test files marked "EXTEND" without listing conflicting pre-M4a tests to remove

**What the spec writes:**
E2 (`instagram-post.test.ts`): "EXTEND" — adds tests for `leadOnSlide === false` on all grid-path text-slides and `leadOnSlide: true` on no-grid Slide-0.
E2b (`instagram-overrides.test.ts`): "EXTEND" — adds tests for `buildManualSlides` outputting `leadOnSlide: false` regardless of stored value.
Files-to-Change `instagram/route.test.ts`: adds 3 new clamp tests (e.g., `?images=5, availableImages=6 → imageCount=4`).

**What a developer will implement incorrectly:**
The existing test suite asserts pre-M4a behavior that directly contradicts the new spec:
- `instagram-post.test.ts` likely has a test asserting `slides[1].leadOnSlide === true` (grid-path, first text-slide, pre-M4a `i === 0 && Boolean(lead)` logic). After A2/A3b changes this becomes `false`. Adding the new test while leaving the old one causes `pnpm test` to fail.
- `instagram-overrides.test.ts` likely asserts that stored `leadOnSlide: true` is preserved on the first grid-path text-slide. The new behavior overrides it to `false`. Conflicting test pair.
- `instagram/route.test.ts` likely has a test asserting `?images=5, availableImages=6 → imageCount=5` (uncapped pre-M4a). After adding `MAX_GRID_IMAGES` clamp, this fails.

Unlike E4 (`instagram-layout/route.test.ts`) which explicitly lists tests to remove/rewrite, E2/E2b and `instagram/route.test.ts` do NOT enumerate which existing tests must be deleted or updated. A developer implementing "EXTEND" literally would leave stale contradicting tests and fail the `pnpm test` gate.

**Missing:** For each of the three test files, list the specific existing tests (by description or behavior) that assert pre-M4a behavior and must be removed or rewritten before adding the new tests.

