## [FAIL] MEDIUM — `TITLE_TO_BODY_GAP` referenced as existing constant but not enumerated in A1b

**What the spec writes:**
A3d uses `TITLE_TO_BODY_GAP` (value 64) in TitleBlock.marginBottom for the no-grid-cover no-lead case:
```tsx
marginBottom={meta.lead ? 0 : TITLE_TO_BODY_GAP}  // (Sonnet R5 #4 — single source-of-truth)
```
The spec calls this "existing pre-M4a behavior" and explicitly says "KEINE neue Property — bestehende Property ändern."

**What a developer will implement incorrectly:**
A1b enumerates exactly 6 existing constants NOT to modify (`HASHTAGS_TO_TITLE_GAP`, `HEADER_TO_BODY_GAP`, `TITLE_TO_GRID_GAP`, `LEAD_TO_BODY_GAP`, `TITLE_TO_LEAD_GAP`, `HEADER_TO_HASHTAGS_GAP`). `TITLE_TO_BODY_GAP` is NOT in this list. If this value is currently inlined as a magic number (e.g., the existing TitleBlock call has `marginBottom={64}` directly), the spec's reference to it as a named constant causes a `TS2304: Cannot find name 'TITLE_TO_BODY_GAP'` compile error. The Sonnet R5 #4 comment ("single source-of-truth") suggests this constant was introduced precisely because the value was inlined — meaning the implementer needs to add it, but the Files-to-Change new-constants list (A1b) does not include it.

**Missing:** Either confirm `TITLE_TO_BODY_GAP = 64` already exists as a named constant in `slide-template.tsx`, OR add it to the Files-to-Change (a) new constants list for `slide-template.tsx`.

