## [FAIL] MEDIUM — LayoutEditor behavior with 0 text-slides not specified after grid-alone-guard removal

**What the spec writes:**
A2c (item (f) in Files-to-Change `instagram-post.ts`) removes the grid-alone-guard from `splitAgendaIntoSlides`. The same guard is removed from `projectAutoBlocksToSlides` (feeds LayoutEditor auto-mode). After this change, an item with `imageCount > 0, non-empty lead, empty body` produces 0 text-slide groups → LayoutEditor receives 0 text-slides to render.

The only LayoutEditor.tsx change is a code comment (Sonnet R5 #5). No logic change. E5 visual-smoke only checks "carousel = 1 Slide (grid-cover), KEIN blank trailing text-slide" (the preview/export), NOT the editor display.

**What a developer will implement incorrectly:**
If `projectAutoBlocksToSlides` previously returned `[[]]` (one empty group, due to the guard) for grid+lead+no-body items, the LayoutEditor rendered a slide-editor for that empty group. After M4a it returns `[]`. If the LayoutEditor accesses `groups[0]` unconditionally or maps without an empty-check, it crashes or renders incorrectly for these items. The spec doesn't verify LayoutEditor's empty-groups rendering path, and the `pnpm test` suite has no component test for `LayoutEditor` with 0 groups (not specified in E2-E5).

**Missing:** Add an E5 visual-smoke check: "Eintrag mit imageCount > 0, non-empty lead, ZERO body-content blocks → LayoutEditor in Auto-Mode zeigt KEINE editierbaren Text-Slides (leerer Zustand, kein crash)". OR add a LayoutEditor component test for the 0-text-slides case.

