## [FAIL] LOW — HeaderRow absent from grid-cover rendering order in Files-to-Change (d)

**What the spec writes:**
Files-to-Change `slide-template.tsx` (d): "rendert in dieser vertikalen Reihenfolge: `<TitleBlock marginTop={HEADER_TO_TITLE_GAP_GRID_COVER} centered />` → `{LeadBlock}` → `<ImageGrid>` → `<HashtagsRow>`"

No HeaderRow is listed.

**What a developer will implement incorrectly:**
The spec's rendering order for the new isFirst grid-cover branch starts directly with TitleBlock. An implementer creating this branch from scratch (rather than modifying the existing code) would omit HeaderRow, producing cover slides without the branding header. The constant name `HEADER_TO_TITLE_GAP_GRID_COVER` implies HeaderRow is present (gap FROM header TO title), but relying on a constant name as the only signal for a required JSX element is fragile.

The existing pure-image branch renders HeaderRow + Hashtags + Title + Grid. After M4a, the cover branch should render HeaderRow + Title + Lead + Grid + Hashtags. HeaderRow must be explicitly listed in (d).

**Missing:** Add `<HeaderRow />` as the first element in the Files-to-Change (d) rendering order for the grid-cover branch.

